It seems that lodash stores a reference to the original function and it's context after calling `_.bind`. This may cause a memory leak. The code is:

```
window.class = function() {
    this.bound = _.bind(this.toBind, this);
}
window.class.prototype.toBind = function() {
    this.value = 'value';
}
window.obj = new window.class()
